    bridge_1014: `—`,
    bridge_15: `—`,
    penny_moment: `Penny is looking forward today. Not at the pile from last week — at what the pile is for. At who your family is becoming. Not the family that worries about money without understanding it. The family that understands it. The family that made a SIP automatic, read the NAV, calculated the real return, kept the promises. That family has a different relationship with money now. Penny can see it in the garden.`,
    penny_mode: `companion`,
    app_text_59: `Look at how much the Money Garden has grown since you started — two cycles of keeping some, letting it grow, watching the numbers, talking about it at dinner. The kind of person who understands money isn't born that way. They just paid attention for long enough. You have. What will you do with that now?`,
    app_text_1014: `Two cycles. 48 weeks of concepts, vocabulary, and conversations. Your portfolio is the physical record of two years of decisions. You understand compounding, real returns, asset allocation, CIBIL scores, the difference between volatility and permanent loss. Most adults don't. What does knowing all of this change about the decisions ahead?`,
    app_text_15: `You have completed two cycles. The portfolio exists. The vocabulary is there. The mechanisms are understood. Cycle 3 is different — it's about applying what you know to real decisions: actual asset allocation choices, real tax planning, active goal reviews. The question isn't what you know. It's what you'll do differently. What is one financial decision your family could make now that you couldn't have made confidently two years ago?`,
